We have a Tauri v2 MCP server now, and it would allow you to check status of the Communitas app. I have copied the MCP server locally, but we need to make some changes so that you can use it. 

And here they are. --- 

1. Add to your Cargo.toml:

toml[dependencies]
tauri-mcp = { git = "https://github.com/P3GLEG/tauri-plugin-mcp" }

2. Update your main.rs:

rustuse tauri_mcp::{PluginConfig, init_with_config};

fn main() {
    tauri::Builder::default()
        #[cfg(debug_assertions)]
        .plugin(init_with_config(
            PluginConfig::new("YourAppName".to_string())
                .tcp("127.0.0.1".to_string(), 4000)
        ))
        .run(tauri::generate_context!())
        .expect("error while running tauri application");
}
